               <head>Grant; Risby, etc.; 31 Ed. III (1357-1358)</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> RISEBY, &amp;c. <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, the abbot of <orgName role="abbot" key="org_104015">St. Edmund of Bury</orgName>
                        </persName>, 
                  grants to the prior and <orgName key="org_104015">convent of St. Edmund</orgName> certain lands, tenements, and rents in 
                  the villages of <placeName key="place_105479">Risby (Rysby)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_104401">Lackford (Lacforde)</placeName>, and 
                  <placeName key="place_105289">Flempton (Flemtone)</placeName> which were formerly <persName>sir <forename>John</forename> de
                  <surname>Rysby</surname>'s, kt.</persName>, to the office of the cellarer for the purpose of keeping an
                  anniversary each year to the memory of the said William. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_104540">Bury St Edmunds (St. Edmund)</placeName> the Sunday next after the feast of All Saints,
                  <origDate notBefore="1357-01-25" notAfter="1358-01-24">31 Ed. III</origDate>. 
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
